This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during an aerial tour of the devastation caused by Hurricane Michael in Lynn Haven, Florida. The President expresses his shock at the extent of the damage, noting that there are no houses left standing. He praises the work of FEMA, first responders, and local government in dealing with the aftermath of the hurricane. The Mayor of Lynn Haven describes his experience during the storm, stating that it felt like a 40-mile-wide EF-3 tornado that lasted for 55 minutes. The President agrees with this assessment and acknowledges the power of the storm. The Administrator also comments on the size and intensity of Hurricane Michael. The Mayor credits their evacuation efforts for preventing any casualties in the town. The remarks conclude with the President expressing his amazement at the situation.